.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.INLEAPYEAR" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.inLeapYear \- Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.inLeapYear
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]inLeapYear\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instances returns a boolean indicating
whether this date is in a leap year.
A leap year is a year that has more days (due to a leap day or leap
month) than a common year.
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
For the ISO 8601 calendar, a leap year is a year that is evenly
divisible by 4, except for years that are evenly divisible by 100,
unless the year is also evenly divisible by 400.
For the ISO 8601 calendar, leap years have 366 days, while common years
have 365 days.
For other calendar systems, the rules likely differ, and leap years may
have more days added (such as a leap month).
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]inLeapYear\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using inLeapYear
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
console.log(date.inLeapYear); \f[I]// false\f[R]
console.log(date.daysInYear); \f[I]// 365\f[R]
console.log(date.monthsInYear); \f[I]// 12\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2020\-07\-01\(dq);
console.log(date2.inLeapYear); \f[I]// true\f[R]
console.log(date2.daysInYear); \f[I]// 366\f[R]
console.log(date2.monthsInYear); \f[I]// 12\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(date3.inLeapYear); \f[I]// false\f[R]
console.log(date3.daysInYear); \f[I]// 354\f[R]
console.log(date3.monthsInYear); \f[I]// 12\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date4 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2023\-07\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(date4.inLeapYear); \f[I]// true\f[R]
console.log(date4.daysInYear); \f[I]// 384\f[R]
console.log(date4.monthsInYear); \f[I]// 13\f[R]
.EE
